sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant F as Frontend (Web UI)
    participant B as Backend API (Flask)
    participant DB as Database (SQLite)
    participant M as Microserver (Flutter)

    Note over U,M: Inventory Outbound Operation - Stock Reduction During Item Sale

    %% Step 1: Sale Initiation
    U->>F: Select items on sales screen
    F->>B: POST /add_sale_record (create sale record)

    %% Step 2: Stock Validation
    B->>DB: SELECT item stock check (SaleItem, SaleItemStockCount)
    DB-->>B: Return stock quantity

    alt Insufficient Stock
        B-->>F: Response: Insufficient stock error
        F-->>U: Display error message
    else Sufficient Stock
        B->>DB: INSERT sale record (SaleRecord)
        B->>DB: INSERT item transaction (SaleItemTransaction)
        B->>DB: UPDATE decrease stock quantity (SaleItemStockCount.current_stock_count -= 1)

        %% Step 3: Stock Status Update
        B->>DB: UPDATE stock status (check re_stock_status)

        %% Step 4: Response Return
        DB-->>B: Update successful
        B-->>F: Response: Sale successful (sale_record, uid)
        F-->>U: Display sale completion message

        %% Step 5: Optional - Microserver Sync
        B->>M: Inventory data sync request (optional)
        M->>DB: SELECT updated inventory data
        DB-->>M: Return inventory data
        M->>M: Update local database (microserver_inventory.db)

        %% Step 6: Real-time UI Update
        F->>B: GET /api/inventory/items (inventory list update request)
        B->>DB: SELECT current inventory status
        DB-->>B: Return inventory data
        B-->>F: Inventory data (JSON)
        F-->>U: Update UI inventory display
    end

    %% Exception Handling
    Note over B,DB: Rollback processing on exceptions
    B->>DB: ROLLBACK (on error occurrence)
    B-->>F: Error response

    %% Audit Logging
    Note over B: All inventory changes are logged
